All incoming 7th grade students who plan to participate in Athletics must have a physical and complete the medical history form and Rank One online forms.

Any 8th grade student that completed an athletic physical last year only needs to complete the medical history form and Rank One online forms.

Forms can be found on the Wharton ISD website (hover on Departments at the top of the page and click on Athletics. The forms/links can be found on the left of the athletics page.

Junior High Athletic practices for football and volleyball will begin on August 17th from 4 pm to 5 pm at the Junior High campus. Social distancing guidelines will be followed. (facial masks are required).

Football at the Junior High football field
Supplies needed:
1. White T-shirt
2. Blue shorts
3. You may wear your own football shoes

Volleyball at the Junior High old and new gym
Supplies needed:
1. White T-shirt
2. Blue shorts
3. Athletic shoes

post_text: This morning, Wharton ISD welcomed back the Wharton ISD Tiger Family during our 2020-2021 Wharton ISD Virtual Convocation. Superintendent, Dr. Michael O'Guin, welcomed back all staff. We would like to say a special thank you to the JROTC and our High School Cheerleaders for being a part of this special event. We would also like to say a special thank you to our Board of Trustee members, Mr. Speer for joining us and Mr. Evans and Mr. Roberts for their special virtual messages that were shared during the convocation. Wharton ISD looks forward to a wonderful, successful school year! Go Tigers!

post_text:
Attention Wharton Tiger Band!

We will proceed with our Summer Band rehearsals starting July 27. We will practice Monday through Friday the weeks leading up to school. We will be following UIL safety protocol. Everyone is required to wear facemasks when applicable; only small sections of the band allowed at a time; the band hall will be disinfected between rehearsals; and when playing instruments, members will maintain 10 feet of space between other members.

The sections will meet at these times:
12:00-1:00 Flutes
1:30- 2:30 Clarinets
3:00-4:00 Saxophones
3:00-5:00 Color Guard
4:30-5:30 Trumpets and Horns
6:00-7:00 Trombones, Euphoniums, and Tubas
7:30-8:30 Percussion

post_text:
2019-2020 Rick Kucera Award

Rick Kucera was a Wharton High School Senior when he tragically drowned in a swimming accident in Matagorda Bay.

Rick played football, basketball, and baseball. He also ran on the track team. He wasn't the best athlete on his teams, but more than made up for it, with his heart and dedication. He was a good student and was active in his community and school.

The Rick Kucera Award winner is awarded to the athlete that not only excels in sports, but also in the classroom. He or she must be a good student and citizen who represents Wharton with integrity and pride.

https://youtu.be/1UnHGchK1_4

post_text:
We would like to thank Coach Eller for her 30 plus years of service to the community and kids of Wharton ISD. Coach Eller has been very successful and earned her place in the Texas Tennis Association Hall of Fame. However, despite the success on the court, Coach Eller had a positive impact on the young men and women she coached over the years. It was my pleasure to work with her and she will be greatly missed. I know she is excited about starting a new chapter and I have no doubt she will continue impacting lives. Best of luck Coach Eller and enjoy the beach life.

Chad Butler
AD/Head Football
Wharton High School

post_text:
Board of Trustees Seek Input on Superintendent Search

The Wharton ISD Board of Trustees is soliciting your input into the current search for our next Superintendent. The Board realizes what a critical component that stakeholder feedback is for this process to be successful. As the Board works on a profile, they will take your input on issues like character, personality traits, experience, and skills needed to be successful, to name a few. The survey will only take a few minutes to complete but will provide valuable feedback for the Board to use as they select candidates to interview. The survey will be posted until May 6th, on the District Website to allow the District time to compile results. Thank you for your time and effort into this important process.

The link to the survey is available below:

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/PYL33P7

WORKING OFFLINE: If your child is using Google Classroom for class, please note they can work on Google (Slides, Docs, Sheets) assignments OFFLINE. So, they can connect to the internet, make documents available offline (see pic), then complete the activity offline. (Open Google File go to File>Make Available Offline for each activity)

This will allow them to make changes (complete the assignment) offline. Then, to turn in, access the internet again and turn in your assignment.

post_text:
Texas Governor Abbott has announced an executive order that closes all schools in Texas until April 3, 2020. This executive order also includes the following:

* No gatherings of more than 10 people.
* No eating/drinking at bars/restaurants, take-out and drive-
thru is acceptable.
* All gyms are closed.
* No visiting nursing homes except for critical care.

This executive order is in place until midnight on April 3, 2020.

We will keep you updated on the closing of the schools and the community of Wharton.

post_text: The Wharton ISD will be holding a special called board meeting on Wednesday, March 18, 2020 at 6:30 PM. The purpose of this meeting is for the Wharton ISD Board of Trustees to hear two grievances/complaints. Public comments for this special called board meeting will be limited to the action items associated with the employee and parent grievances/complaints as posted on the agenda. Other public comments will be allowed at the regular scheduled monthly board meeting scheduled for Tuesday, March 24, 2020.

post_text: Attention all parents: The Wharton ISD was informed this morning, Monday, January 27, 2020, that a threat has been made upon all campuses. At this time in an abundance of caution, all campuses have been placed on lockout to prevent any visitors from entering campuses. The source of the threat has not been identified at this time. The WISD Police Department is working with the City of Wharton Police Department to identify the source of the threat. At this time, all students and staff are safely inside the building. We will keep parents and community members updated as we receive additional information.

Wharton Police Department
January 17 at 3:56 PM Â·

### PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENT ### PLEASE READ ###

In an effort to meet the constitutional and legislative requirements to count the U.S. population, in preparation for the upcoming 2020 decennial census, members of the census bureau will be out in our community from January 16, 2020 and continue though March 30, 2020.

Field staff will be knocking on doors in order to verify addresses and gather information.

Census employees can be identified by the laptop computer with a census bureau logo on the top, a black canvass bag with a census logo and photo identification card.

If you have any questions, please call 301 763-1716 and a member of the office of security will assist you.
text:
Wharton Police Department
January 17 at 3:56 PM Â·

### PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENT ### PLEASE READ ###

In an effort to meet the constitutional and legislative requirements to count the U.S. population, in preparation for the upcoming 2020 decennial census, members of the census bureau will be out in our community from January 16, 2020 and continue though March 30, 2020.

Field staff will be knocking on doors in order to verify addresses and gather information.

Census employees can be identified by the laptop computer with a census bureau logo on the top, a black canvass bag with a census logo and photo identification card.

If you have any questions, please call 301 763-1716 and a member of the office of security will assist you.

EDUCATORS - This one is for you!

While SeaWorld calls it a "teacher" card, the offer is valid for anyone who has been certified by the state of Texas for grades Pre-Kâ€“12. There is an online application process, but it only takes about 10 minutes to complete.

To register go to https://seaworld.com/san-antonio/tickets/teacher-card/.

Wharton High School Tiger Basetball teams had a great night!

This week, they battled against Sealy at home. The boys won 72-40 and are now 12-2 on the season and 1-1 in district. Our Girls won 36-32 and are now 11-5 on the season and 3-1 in district.

GO TIGERS! #WeAreWharton

post_text: The weather is changing, please stay safe!
shared_text:
Wharton County Office of Emergency Management
January 10 at 4:53 PM Â·

DO YOU LIVE IN A MOBILE HOME OR TRAVEL TRAILER
IN WHARTON COUNTY?

Severe thunderstorms can produce winds in excess of what your mobile home or travel trailer can safely withstand. Make plans NOW where you will go if high winds are forecast for our area. There are no severe weather shelters in Wharton County, so you must be ready to take care of your own life and property.

Ask yourself these questions:

HOW WILL YOU KNOW SEVERE WEATHER IS APPROACHING?

WHERE WILL YOU GO IF YOU DO LEAVE?

HOW MUCH TIME WILL YOU NEED TO EVACUATE IF YOU PLAN TO LEAVE?

Weather information is available on local radio stations KIOX 96.1 FM, KULP 1390 AM and FM 106.7, and local newspapers and TV stations. THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE WEBSITE IS WEATHER.GOV/HGX.

YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR SAFETY.

MAKE PLANS NOW.

Wharton Police Department
January 4 at 12:57 AM Â·

Today, Chief Lynch, along with several members of our department, presented Caleb Moreno, of KPRW2 Wharton, with a new bicycle (KPRW2â€™s newest response vehicle), to honor his volunteerism within our community. His old bike had seen better days.

Caleb, a freshman in High School, exemplifies our town best through drive, determination and best of all, his willingness to invest his time on those that make our city great: its citizens!
